# Tailwind Usage Rules (Stronger Enforcement)

## Allowed

- Layout utilities (`flex`, `grid`, etc.)
- Spacing utilities (`p-4`, `mt-2`, `gap-3`, etc.)
- Border/radius/shadow utilities

## Not Allowed

- Arbitrary values (e.g. `p-[13px]`)
- Color utilities for scales **not** defined in `src/styles/tokens/colors.css` (e.g. stock `text-green-500` if green isn’t in the project file)
- Hardcoded color values:
  - no `#hex`, `rgb()`, `rgba()`, `hsl()` in inline styles
  - no hardcoded colors in CSS/SCSS/style props

## Colors (project palette)

- Use Tailwind color utilities that map to `src/styles/tokens/colors.css` (e.g. `gray-25` … `gray-950`, `primary-600`, `border-gray-200`). Do not add a parallel “semantic name” layer unless explicitly requested.
- Do **not** use default Tailwind palette names that are not in this project’s `colors.css` unless those scales are added there first.
- Do **not** add `dark:` variants or theme toggles; the app is light-only.

## Class name merging

- In components (and anywhere Tailwind classes are composed), use **`twMerge`** from `tailwind-merge` for every `className` value, including internal subtrees (icons, children wrappers), not only the root when a `className` prop exists.
- Do **not** use a project-local `cx`/`cn` that only concatenates strings unless it wraps `twMerge` (this repo standard is `twMerge` directly).
- Pass conditional pieces as `condition && "classes"`; `twMerge` accepts falsy entries per its `ClassNameValue` typing.

